window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Lights. Camera. Murder.</p> <p>Amidst the rugged beauty of Oregon's Opal Creek Wilderness, a contestant on a reality survival show falls to his death from an isolated cliff, his body later devoured by black bears. The show's producers are spinning it as a tragic accident, but local police suspect murder.</p> <p>While enjoying a leisurely tour of the Oregon wine country, Detective Thomas Austin is drawn into the mystery when he learns that the deceased is a well-known author who lived minutes from his own home. Joining the investigations, Austin must navigate conflicting stories from the show's crew and contestants along with protestors, paparazzi, a local tribe, and even Bigfoot hunters. As Austin delves deeper into the dark secrets of the reality show and its participants, he uncovers a web of lies and hidden agendas that threaten to consume him.</p> <p>And when a crew member vanishes, the investigation takes a turn more twisted and sinister than Austin could have imagined. In a world where reality is just another carefully crafted performance, lines between truth and fiction begin to blur.</p> <p>With time running out and the murderer always one step ahead, can Austin separate fact from fiction and catch the killer before it's too late?</p> <p>Series List (can be listened to in any order):</p> <p>Book 1: The Bones at Point No Point</p> <p>Book 2: The Shadows of Pike Place</p> <p>Book 3: The Fallen of Foulweather Bluff</p> <p>Book 4: The Horror at Murden Cove</p> <p>Book 5: The Terror in the Emerald City</p> <p>Book 6: The Drowning at Dyes Inlet</p> <p>Book 7: The Nightmare at Manhattan Beach</p> <p>Book 8: The Silence at Mystery Bay</p> <p>Book 9: The Darkness at Deception Pass</p> <p>Book 10: The Vanishing at Opal Creek</p> <p>Book 11: The Secrets of Second Beach (available for pre-order)</p>"; 
